6x7,68, and comes with 5th generation Broadwell Processors, a 1 TB HDD, and 8 GB of RAM.<ref>[http://us-store.acer.com/aspire-r3-471t-77ht-convertible-notebook Aspire R3-471T-77HT Convertible Notebook.], Retrieved on 2015-07-31</ref>\n\n=== Aspire R7 ===\nThe [[Acer Aspire R7]] (model R7-572-...) is a 15.6-inch convertible (2-in-1) laptop with a single-hinge \"Ezel\" folding design. It has a display resolution of 1,920x1,080 and N-Trig DuoSense technology stylus support. It comes with 4th generation Haswell Processors, a 1 TB HDD, and 8 GB of RAM.<ref>[https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2453578,00.asp Acer Aspire R7-572-6423.], Retrieved on 2015-07-29</ref><ref>[http://www.cnet.com/products/acer-aspire-r7/ Acer Aspire R7 review: An experimental laptop that both hits and misses.], Retrieved on 2015-07-29</ref>\n\n=== Aspire R 13 ===\nThe Acer Aspire (model R7-371t-...) is a 13.3\" convertible (2-in-1) laptop with a double-hinge \"Ezel\" folding design. It has two available display resolutions of 1,920x1,080 or 2,560x1,440, and Synaptics stylus support. It comes with either 4th generation Haswell, 5th generation Broadwell Processors or 6th generation Skylake processors, solid state hard drives in sizes of 128, 256, or 512 GB, and 8 GB of RAM.<ref>[http://www.notebookreview.com/notebookreview/acer-aspire-r13-review/ Acer Aspire R13 Review.], Retrieved on 2015-07-29</ref><ref>[http://www.digitaltrends.com/laptop-reviews/acer-aspire-r13-review/ ACER ASPIRE R13 REVIEW.], Retrieved on 2015-07-29</ref>\n\n=== Aspire R 15 ===\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name         = Acer Aspire R15\n| title        = \n| aka          = Aspire R15\n| logo         = \n| image        = Acer promotional model with laptop at Computex 20160531.jpg\n| caption      = \n| developer    = [[Acer Inc.|Acer]]\n| manufacturer = [[Acer Inc.|Acer]]\n| family       = \n| type         = [[2-in-1 PC]]\n| generation   = \n| releasedate  = 2015\n| lifespan     = \n| price        = \n| discontinued = 