\u00fcr Einsteiger: Acer Aspire S3 im Test] (german). Retrieved on 2012-03-17.</ref> Overall, the Ultrabook weighs 2.98 pounds.\n\n=== Aspire S5 ===\nThe Acer Aspire S5 is a 13.3-Inch Ultrabook, which the company says is the world's thinnest Ultrabook.<ref>[http://us.acer.com/ac/en/US/press/2012/28709 Acer Unveils World's Thinnest Ultrabook: Aspire S5] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419043750/http://us.acer.com/ac/en/US/press/2012/28709 |date=2012-04-19 }}, Acer Inc. Retrieved on 2012-02-17.</ref> It is just 15mm-thick and so two millimeters thinner than the [[MacBook Air]].<ref>[http://t3n.de/news/acer-legt-vor-ultradunnes-aspire-356613/ Acer presents: Ultra-thin notebook and Aspire S5 Full-HD Quad Core Tablet Iconia A700] (german), t3n. Retrieved on 2012-03-17.</ref> It weighs 2.97 pounds and includes an Intel Ivy Bridge processor, 8&nbsp;GB of DDR3 RAM, SSD storage for speed and increased shock resistance plus professionally tuned Dolby\u00ae Home Theater\u00ae v4.\n\n=== Aspire S7 ===\nThe Acer Aspire S7 is a 13.3-inch ultrabook, a successor to the Aspire S5. It uses the same aluminum frame wrapping a pearly white plastic and Gorilla Glass encasement and is able to bend backwards 180 degrees and lie flat. It weighs roughly less than 1.3&nbsp;kg and includes an Intel Ivy Bridge processor, 8&nbsp;GB of DDR3 RAM, SSD storage for speed and increased shock resistance plus professionally tuned Dolby Home Theater\u00ae v4.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnet.com/products/acer-aspire-s7-392-6411/|title=Acer Aspire S7-392-6411 review|publisher=Cnet}}</ref>\n\n=== Aspire S13 ===\nThe Acer Aspire S13 is a 13.3-inch ultrabook, a successor to the Aspire S7. The computer has an Intel Core i5 dual-core processor, 1080p display, SSD storage, [[USB-C]] port, and 8GB of ram.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/laptop-reviews/acer-aspire-s-13-2016-review/|title=Acer Aspire S 13 (2016) review|date=15 June 2016|website=Digital Trends|last1=Smith|first1=Matt|accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire Timeline series == \n{{Main|Acer Aspire Timeline}}\nAcer [[Aspire Timeline]] is a discontinued sub-line of the Aspire series which consisted of [[ultrabook]]s. The indirect successor to the Aspire Timeline's are the [[Acer Swift]] lineup.  {{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire V Nitro series ==\n'''List of Acer Aspire V Nitro series models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n*VN7-571\n*VN7-571G\n*VN7-572\n*VN7-572G\n*VN7-572TG\n*VN7-591G\n*VN7-592G\n*VN7-593G\n*VN7-791G\n*VN7-792G\n*VN7-793G{{div col end}}\n\n== Aspire V series ==\n'''List of Acer Aspire V series models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n*V3-111P\n*V3-112P\n*V3-331\n*V3-371\n*V3-372\n*V3-372T\n*V3-431\n*V3-471\n*V3-471G\n*V3-472\n*V3-472G\n*V3-472P\n*V3-472PG\n*V3-531\n*V3-531G\n*V3-532\n*V3-532G\n*V3-551\n*V3-551G\n*V3-571\n*V3-571G\n*V3-572\n*V3-572G\n*V3-572P\n*V3-572PG\n*V3-574\n*V3-574G\n*V3-574T\n*V3-574TG\n*V3-575\n*V3-575G\n*V3-575T\n*V3-575TG\n*V3-731\n*V3-731G\n*V3-771\n*V3-7710\n*V3-7710G\n*V3-771G\n*V3-772G\n* V5-121\n* V5-122P\n* V5-123\n* V5-131\n* V5-132\n* V5-132P\n* V5-171\n* V5-431\n* V5-431G\n* V5-431P\n* V5-431PG\n* V5-452G\n* V5-452PG\n* V5-471\n* V5-471G\n* V5-471P\n* V5-471PG\n* V5-472\n* V5-472G\n* V5-472P\n* V5-472PG\n* V5-473\n* V5-473G\n* V5-473P\n* V5-473PG\n* V5-531\n* V5-531G\n* V5-531P\n* V5-531PG\n* V5-551\n* V5-551G\n* V5-552\n* V5-552G\n* V5-552P\n* V5-552PG\n* V5-561\n* V5-561G\n* V5-561P\n* V5-561PG\n* V5-571\n* V5-571G\n* V5-571P\n* V5-571PG\n* V5-572\n* V5-572G\n* V5-572P\n* V5-572PG\n* V5-573\n* V5-573G\n* V5-573P\n* V5-573PG\n* V5-591G\n* V7-481\n* V7-481G\n* V7-481P\n* V7-481PG\n* V7-482P\n* V7-482PG\n* V7-581\n* V7-581G\n* V7-581P\n* V7-581PG\n* V7-582P\n* V7-582PG\n{{div col end}}The Acer Aspire V series consists of the Acer Aspire V, Acer Aspire V3, Acer Aspire V5, Acer Aspire V 13 and Acer Aspire V15.\n\n=== Aspire V5 ===\n[[File:Acer Aspire V5 20121030.jpg|thumb|Acer Aspire V5]]\n\nThe Acer Aspire V5 is notebook available in 14 and 15.6 inches and comes with a silver scratch resistant exterior. It is considerably slim and is offered in both 10-point multi-touch and non-touch variants. The V5 comes with a HD display with a resolution of 1366\u00d7768 pixels and a webcam on top. The left consists of a power slot, the heat-sink, a proprietary slot to plug-in the adaptor for the Gigabit Ethernet port and the VGA port, an HDMI slot, a USB 3.0 port, two USB 2.0 ports and a 3.5&nbsp;mm headphone jack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultrabooked.com/reviews/1/acer-aspire-v5-specs-review|title=Acer Aspire V5 specs review - Ultrabooked|website=www.ultrabooked.com|access-date=2018-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170428072658/http://www.ultrabooked.com/reviews/1/acer-aspire-v5-specs-review|archive-date=2017-04-28|url-status=dead}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire VX series ==\n\n=== Aspire VX 15 ===\nThe Acer Aspire VX 15 specifications includes the use of either an Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 i5-7300HQ or an Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 i7-7700HQ, 8GB or 16GB DDR4 SDRAM, a 15.6\" Full HD (1920 x 1080) 16:9 and either a NVIDIA\u00ae GeForce\u00ae GTX 1050 with 4 GB Dedicated Memory or a NVIDIA\u00ae GeForce\u00ae GTX 1050Ti with 4 GB Dedicated Memory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.acer.com/ac/en/US/content/models/laptops/aspirevx15|title=Laptops {{!}} View All Our Laptops {{!}} Acer Solutions|website=www.acer.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n=== Aspire VX 5 ===\nThe Acer Aspire VX 5 specifications includes the use of either an Intel Core i7-7700HQ, 8GB DDR4 SDRAM, single-channel, a 15.6 inch 16:9, 1920 x 1080 pixel 141 PPI HD and either a NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1050 Ti (Laptop) - 4096 MB, Core: 1493 - 1620&nbsp;MHz.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.acer-us.com/Tm90ZWJvb2skJEFzcGlyZQ==_2_Aspire/|title=Acer Aspire Laptops List  {{!}} View All Our Laptops {{!}} Acer Solutions|website=www.acer-us.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-18}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n== Other models  ==\n'''List of other Acer Aspire models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n*One\n*1200\n*1300\n*1350\n*1360\n*1400\n*1410 (11.6\")\n*1420P\n*1430\n*1430Z\n*1500\n*1520\n*1551\n*1640\n*1640Z\n*1650\n*1660\n*1670\n*1680\n*1690\n*1700\n*1710\n*1800\n*1810T\n*1810TZ\n*1820PT\n*1830\n*1830T\n*1830TZ\n*2000\n*2010\n*2020\n*2420\n*2430\n*2920\n*2920Z\n*2930\n*2930Z\n*3000\n*3050\n*3100\n*3500\n*3600\n*3610\n*3620\n*3630\n*3640\n*3650\n*3660\n*3680\n*3690\n*3750\n*3750G\n*3750Z\n*3750ZG\n*3810T\n*3810TZ\n*3820T\n*3820TG\n*3820TZ\n*3830\n*3830G\n*3830\n*3830G\n*3830T\n*3830TG\n*3935\n*4220\n*4230\n*4250\n*4251\n*4252\n*4253\n*4310\n*4315\n*4320\n*4330\n*4332\n*4333\n*4336\n*4339\n*4349\n*4350\n*4350G\n*4352\n*4352G\n*4410\n*4520\n*4520G\n*4530\n*4535\n*4535G\n*4540\n*4540G\n*4551\n*4551G\n*4552\n*4552G\n*4553\n*4553G\n*4560\n*4560G\n*4625G\n*4710\n*4710G\n*4710Z\n*4710ZG\n*4715Z\n*4720\n*4720G\n*4720Z\n*4720ZG\n*4730\n*4730Z\n*4730ZG\n*4732Z\n*4733Z\n*4735Z\n*4735ZG\n*4736\n*4736G\n*4736Z\n*4736ZG\n*4738\n*4738G\n*4738Z\n*4738ZG\n*4739\n*4739Z\n*4740\n*4740G\n*4741\n*4741G\n*4741ZG\n*4743\n*4743Z\n*4745\n*4745G\n*4745Z\n*4749\n*4749Z\n*4750\n*4750G\n*4750Z\n*4750ZG\n*4752\n*4752G\n*4752Z\n*4752ZG\n*4755\n*4755G\n*4810T\n*4810TG\n*4810TZ\n*4810TZG\n*4820\n*4820G\n*4820T\n*4820TG\n*4820TZ\n*4820TZG\n*4830\n*4830G\n*4830T\n*4830TG\n*4830Z\n*4920\n*4920G\n*4925\n*4925G\n*4930\n*4930G\n*4930ZG\n*4935\n*4935G\n*4937\n*4937G\n*5000\n*5010\n*5020\n*5030\n*5040\n*5050\n*5100\n*5110\n*5220\n*5230\n*5235\n*5250\n*5251\n*5252\n*5253\n*5310\n*5315\n*5320\n*5330\n*5332\n*5333\n*5334\n*5335\n*5336\n*5338\n*5342\n*5349\n*5350\n*5410\n*5500\n*5500Z\n*5510\n*5515\n*5516\n*5517\n*5520\n*5520G\n*5530\n*5530G\n*5532\n*5534\n*5535\n*5536\n*5536G\n*5538\n*5538G\n*5540\n*5541G\n*5542\n*5542G\n*5550\n*5551\n*5551G\n*5552\n*5552G\n*5553\n*5553G\n*5560 (15'')\n*5560G\n*5570\n*5570Z\n*5580\n*5590\n*5600\n*5610\n*5610Z\n*5620\n*5