e=nl|last1=Burger|first1=Julie|access-date=2018-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517185218/http://bluedigit.nl/laptops|archive-date=2017-05-17|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Aspire 5738 ===\nAcer Aspire 5738 is a [[dual boot|dual-booting]] ([[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[MS-Windows]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcpro.co.uk/blogs/2009/10/14/acer-3d-laptop-review-first-look/|title=Acer 3D laptop review: first look|publisher=}}</ref> 3D laptop, which includes Dynamic Digital Depth TriDef software.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2009/10/21/acers-3d-equipped-aspire-5738dg-laptop-gets-official-examined/|title=Acer's 3D-equipped Aspire 5738DG laptop gets official, examined|last=Melanson|first=Donald|publisher=Engadget}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2009/10/28/ddd_acer_3d_laptop/|title=Hands on with Acer's 3D laptop|last2=tweet_btn()|first2=James Sherwood|publisher=|first1=28 Oct 2009 at|last1=10:23}}</ref>\n\nThe Acer Aspire 5738PG computer also includes the Acer [[multi-touch]] technology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://us.acer.com/showrooms/touch/touchscreen.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100111031106/http://us.acer.com/showrooms/touch/touchscreen.html|url-status=dead|title=Acer Official Site: Technology - Acer Touch<!-- Bot generated title -->|archivedate=January 11, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/slideshow/318267/acer-launches-new-touch-screen-monitor-notebooks/|title=Acer launches new touch-screen monitor, notebooks|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.acer.com/ Acer Official Website]\n\n{{Acer Inc.}}\n\n[[Category:Acer products]]\n[[Category:Personal computers]]\n[[Category:Laptops]]\n[[Category:Acer laptops]]\n[[Category:Consumer electronics brands]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Acer Aspire desktops}}\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| image        = Acer Aspire 5735z.jpg\n| developer    = [[Acer Inc.|Acer]]\n| type         = [[Laptop computer|Laptop]]\n| connectivity = Ethernet LAN, Wi-Fi\n| media        = \n| OS           = {{nowrap|[[Windows 2000]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.acer.com/ac/en/US/content/support-product/68?b=1|title=Product Support &#124; Acer United States|website=www.acer.com}}</ref>}}, {{nowrap|[[Windows XP]]}}, {{nowrap|[[Windows Vista]]}}, {{nowrap|[[Windows 7]]}}, {{nowrap|[[Windows 8]]}}, {{nowrap|[[Windows 8.1]]}}, {{nowrap|[[Windows 10]]}}\n| input        = USB 2.0, USB 3.0, card reader, audio microphone \n| camera       = HD webcam\n| memory       = 2&nbsp;GB, 4&nbsp;GB, 6&nbsp;GB, 8&nbsp;GB\n| power        = \n| processor    = Intel, AMD\n| display      = HD Widescreen CineCrystal \n| dimensions   = \n| weight       =  \n}}\n\n'''Acer Aspire''' (stylized as '''\u039bspire''' or '''\u039bSPIRE''') is a series of [[personal computer]]s by [[Acer Inc.]] aimed at the casual household user or for small business use. The Aspire series covers both [[desktop computer]]s and [[laptop]]s. Acer developed the series in order to cover from essentials to high performances.<ref>{{cite web|title=Acer Aspire Series |url=http://www.laptopspedia.com/Acer_Aspire/ |publisher=Laptopspedia |date=2010-06-01 |accessdate=2010-06-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100608174609/http://www.laptopspedia.com/Acer_Aspire |archivedate=June 8, 2010 }}</ref>\n\nMany of the Aspire laptops, such as model 8920G, have built in [[Blu-ray Disc|Blu-ray]] drives, 5.1 audio outputs and [[transflective]] displays. Acer was the first to include these drives in laptops. Most Aspire laptops have water-resistant screens, such as the 1410 and the 5741 Z.{{Citation needed|date=October 2018}}\n\nIn 2007, Acer introduced the [[Gemstone series]] that marked a milestone in the Acer Aspire line.\n\nLike with many [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] laptops, different models may have different specification in different parts of the world.\n\n== Aspire series ==\n'''List of Acer Aspire series models'''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.acer.com/ac/en/US/content/drivers|title=Download Drivers and Manuals {{!}} Acer Official Site|website=www.acer.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-17}}</ref>{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n* A111-31\n* A114-31\n* A114-32\n* A311-31\n* A314-31\n* A314-32\n* A314-33\n* A314-41\n* A315-21\n* A315-21G\n* A315-31\n* A315-32\n* A315-33\n* A315-41\n* A315-41G\n* A315-51\n* A315-52\n* A315-53\n* A315-53G\n* A514-51\n* A514-51G\n* A514-51K\n* A515-41G\n* A515-51\n* A515-51G\n* A515-52\n* A515-52G\n* A515-53\n* A515-53G\n* A517-51\n* A517-51G\n* A517-51GP\n* A517-51P\n* A615-51\n* A615-51G\n* A715-71G\n* A715-72G\n* A717-71G\n* A717-72G{{div col end}}The Aspire series was introduced in 2017 with four main models: 1, 3, 5 and 7.\n\nDespite similarities with the Aspire E series, in many regions, the Aspire series is sold alongside the Aspire E series.\n\nIn 2018, the Aspire 6 was launched exclusively for Malaysia. The Aspire 6 is simply an Aspire 5 with a Captain America inspired aesthetics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lowyat.net/2018/160758/acer-launches-avengers-infinity-war-special-edition-laptops-in-malaysia-retails-from-rm3299/|title=Acer Launches Avengers: Infinity War Special Edition Laptops in Malaysia; Retails from RM3,299 - Lowyat.NET|website=www.lowyat.net|language=en-US|access-date=2018-10-10}}</ref>\n\nThe Aspire 5 was originally launched with [[Kaby Lake|Intel Kaby Lake]] processors (i5-7200u and i7-7500u) and then was updated with [[Kaby Lake#List of 8th generation Kaby Lake R processors|Kaby Lake R]] processors (i5-8250u and i7-8550u) and more recently updated with [[Whiskey Lake (microarchitecture)|Whisky Lake]] processors (i3-8145u, i5-8265u and i7-8565u) which came along with a redesign which involved slimmer bezels but dedicated maintenance panels for RAM and storage was omitted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.notebookcheck.net/Acer-Aspire-5-A515-52G-i5-8265U-MX150-SSD-FHD-Laptop-Review.354441.0.html|title=Acer Aspire 5 A515-52G (i5-8265U, MX150, SSD, FHD) Laptop Review|last=M\u00f6lck|first=Sascha|website=Notebookcheck|language=en|access-date=2019-03-04}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire E series ==\n'''List of Acer Aspire E series models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n*E1-410\n*E1-410G\n*E1-411G\n*E1-422\n*E1-422G\n*E1-430\n*E1-430G\n*E1-430P\n*E1-431\n*E1-431G\n*E1-432\n*E1-432G\n*E1-432P\n*E1-451G\n*E1-470\n*E1-470G\n*E1-470P\n*E1-470PG\n*E1-471\n*E1-471G\n*E1-472\n*E1-472G\n*E1-472P\n*E1-472PG\n*E1-510\n*E1-510P\n*E1-521\n*E1-522\n*E1-530\n*E1-530G\n*E1-531\n*E1-531G\n*E1-532\n*E1-532G\n*E1-532P\n*E1-532PG\n*E1-570\n*E1-570G\n*E1-571\n*E1-571G\n*E1-572\n*E1-572G\n*E1-572P\n*E1-572PG\n*E1-731\n*E1-731G\n*E1-732G\n*E1-771\n*E1-771G\n*E1-772\n*E1-772G\n*E3-111\n*E3-112\n*E3-112M\n*E5-411\n*E5-411G\n*E5-421\n*E5-421G\n*E5-422\n*E5-422G\n*E5-432\n*E5-432G\n*E5-452G\n*E5-471\n*E5-471G\n*E5-471P\n*E5-471PG\n*E5-472G\n*E5-473\n*E5-473G\n*E5-473T\n*E5-473TG\n*E5-474\n*E5-474G\n*E5-475\n*E5-475G\n*E5-476\n*E5-476G\n*E5-491G\n*E5-511\n*E5-511G\n*E5-511P\n*E5-521\n*E5-521G\n*E5-522\n*E5-522G\n*E5-523\n*E5-523G\n*E5-531\n*E5-531G\n*E5-531P\n*E5-532\n*E5-532G\n*E5-532T\n*E5-551\n*E5-551G\n*E5-552\n*E5-552G\n*E5-553\n*E5-553G\n*E5-571\n*E5-571G\n*E5-571P\n*E5-571PG\n*E5-572G\n*E5-573\n*E5-573G\n*E5-573T\n*E5-573TG\n*E5-574\n*E5-574G\n*E5-574T\n*E5-574TG\n*E5-575\n*E5-575G\n*E5-575T\n*E5-575TG\n*E5-576\n*E5-576G\n*E5-721\n*E5-722\n*E5-722G\n*E5-731\n*E5-731G\n*E5-752\n*E5-752G\n*E5-771\n*E5-771G\n*E5-772\n*E5-772G\n*E5-773\n*E5-773G\n*E5-774\n*E5-774G\n*EC-470G\n*EC-471G\n*EK-571G\n*ES1-111\n*ES1-111M\n*ES1-131\n*ES1-132\n*ES1-311\n*ES1-331\n*ES1-332\n*ES1-411\n*ES1-420\n*ES1-421\n*ES1-422\n*ES1-431\n*ES1-432\n*ES1-433\n*ES1-433G\n*ES1-511\n*ES1-512\n*ES1-520\n*ES1-521\n*ES1-522\n*ES1-523\n*ES1-524\n*ES1-531\n*ES1-532G\n*ES1-533\n*ES1-571\n*ES1-572\n*ES1-711\n*ES1-711G\n*ES1-731\n*ES1-731G\n*ES1-732\n*VSF-069{{div col end}}\n[[File:Acer Aspire E5-432-C7LD 20161109.jpg|thumb|Acer Aspire E15]]\nThe Acer's Aspire E series also contains the Aspire ES sub series. The Aspire E comes with either a 14\" or 15.6\" 16:9 display named E14 and E15 respectively. The Aspire ES comes with either an 11.6\" or 14\" 16:9 display named ES11 and ES14 respectively.\n\nThe Aspire E series has been updated annually with newer Intel Processors. The Aspire E series is currently offered with Intel [[Kaby Lake|8th]] generation Intel Core i series processors but has been offered with [[Haswell (microarchitecture)|4th]], [[Broadwell (microarchitecture)|5th]], [[Skylake (microarchitecture)|6th]] and [[Kaby Lake|7th]] generation Intel Core i series processors.\n\nThe Aspire E15 and Aspire 5 are similar but different.\n\nThe Aspire E15 weighs 5.27&nbsp;lb and its dimensions are: 15.02\" x 10.20\" x 1.19\". It has a SD Card slot, 2x USB 3.0 Type-A ports, 1x USB 2.0 Type-A port, RJ-45 Ethernet network port, HDMI Output, 1x USB 3.1 Type-C port and 1x VGA Port.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Reception\n!Year\n!Model\n!Publisher\n!Rating\n!Citation\n|-\n|2014\n|N/A\n|Tech Radar\n|{{Rating|3.5|5}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.techradar.com/reviews/pc-mac/laptops-portable-pcs/laptops-and-netbooks/acer-aspire-e15-2014-1284546/review|title=Acer Aspire E15 (2014)|work=TechRadar|access-date=2018-10-10|language=EN-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\n|E5-575-33BM\n|Laptop Mag\n|{{Rating|4|5}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.laptopmag.com/reviews/laptops/acer-aspire-e-15-e5-575-33bm|title=Acer Aspire E 15 (E5-575-33BM) Review|access-date=2018-10-10}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|E5-576G-5762\n|Digital Trends\n|{{Rating|4|5}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.digitaltrends.com/laptop-reviews/acer-aspire-e-15-review/|title=Acer Aspire E 15 Review {{!}} Digital Trends|date=2018-07-28|work=Digital Trends|access-date=2018-10-10|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|N/A\n|Tech Radar\n|{{Rating|4|5}}\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ww