spire subcompact notebooks ([[netbook]]s) similar to the [[Asus EEE]].{{Clear}}\n\n==Aspire P series==\n'''List of Acer Aspire P series models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n* P3-131\n* P3-171{{div col end}}\n\n=== Aspire P3 ===\nThe Acer Aspire P3 is an 11.6-inch IPS LCD textured titanium-alloy maid ultrabook with an Intel Core i3-3229Y 1.4&nbsp;GHz processor for i3 models and Intel Core i5-3329Y 1.5&nbsp;GHz processor for i5 Models, 128&nbsp;GB Solid State Drive, Bluetooth and Wi-Fi connectivity in 9.9&nbsp;mm thin profile and a 2 or 4&nbsp;GB of RAM. It also has one ventilation fan inside to cool the ultrabook when it is heavily used. This ultrabook was listed as a top-5 hybrid convertible laptop of 2013 by TechRadar.com.{{citation needed|date=September 2015}}{{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire R series ==\n'''List of Acer Aspire R series models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n*R3-131T\n*R3-431T\n*R3-471T\n*R3-471TG\n*R5-371T\n*R5-431T\n*R5-471T\n*R5-571T\n*R5-571TG\n*R7-371T\n*R7-372T\n*R7-571\n*R7-571G\n*R7-572\n*R7-572G\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Aspire R 11 ===\nThe [[Acer Aspire R 11]] (model R3-131-...) is an 11-inch convertible (2-in-1) laptop with a mainstream folding design, similar to the [[Asus Transformer Book Flip TP200]], Dell Inspiron 11 3000 Series 2-in-1, HP Pavilion x360, [[HP Stream x360]], [[Lenovo Yoga 2 11]], [[Lenovo Yoga 3 11|3 11]] and [[Toshiba Satellite Radius 11]].\n\n=== Aspire R 14 ===\nThe [[Acer Aspire R 14]] (model R3-471T-...) is a 14-inch convertible (2-in-1) laptop with a mainstream folding design, similar to the [[Lenovo Yoga 3 14]] laptop. It has a display resolution of 1,366x7,68, and comes with 5th generation Broadwell Processors, a 1 TB HDD, and 8 GB of RAM.<ref>[http://us-store.acer.com/aspire-r3-471t-77ht-convertible-notebook Aspire R3-471T-77HT Convertible Notebook.], Retrieved on 2015-07-31</ref>\n\n=== Aspire R7 ===\nThe [[Acer Aspire R7]] (model R7-572-...) is a 15.6-inch convertible (2-in-1) laptop with a single-hinge \"Ezel\" folding design. It has a display resolution of 1,920x1,080 and N-Trig DuoSense technology stylus support. It comes with 4th generation Haswell Processors, a 1 TB HDD, and 8 GB of RAM.<ref>[https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2453578,00.asp Acer Aspire R7-572-6423.], Retrieved on 2015-07-29</ref><ref>[http://www.cnet.com/products/acer-aspire-r7/ Acer Aspire R7 review: An experimental laptop that both hits and misses.], Retrieved on 2015-07-29</ref>\n\n=== Aspire R 13 ===\nThe Acer Aspire (model R7-371t-...) is a 13.3\" convertible (2-in-1) laptop with a double-hinge \"Ezel\" folding design. It has two available display resolutions of 1,920x1,080 or 2,560x1,440, and Synaptics stylus support. It comes with either 4th generation Haswell, 5th generation Broadwell Processors or 6th generation Skylake processors, solid state hard drives in sizes of 128, 256, or 512 GB, and 8 GB of RAM.<ref>[http://www.notebookreview.com/notebookreview/acer-aspire-r13-review/ Acer Aspire R13 Review.], Retrieved on 2015-07-29</ref><ref>[http://www.digitaltrends.com/laptop-reviews/acer-aspire-r13-review/ ACER ASPIRE R13 REVIEW.], Retrieved on 2015-07-29</ref>\n\n=== Aspire R 15 ===\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name         = Acer Aspire R15\n| title        = \n| aka          = Aspire R15\n| logo         = \n| image        = Acer promotional model with laptop at Computex 20160531.jpg\n| caption      = \n| developer    = [[Acer Inc.|Acer]]\n| manufacturer = [[Acer Inc.|Acer]]\n| family       = \n| type         = [[2-in-1 PC]]\n| generation   = \n| releasedate  = 2015\n| lifespan     = \n| price        = \n| discontinued = \n| unitssold    = \n| unitsshipped = \n| media        = \n| os           = [[Windows 10]]\n| power        = 4-cell non-removable lithium-ion battery\n| soc          = \n| cpu          = Intel\u00ae Core i5 or i7\n| memory       = 8GB\n| storage      = 1TB\n| memory card  = \n| display      = 15.6\"<br>Full HD (1920 x 1080) resolution\n| graphics     = Intel HD Graphics 520<br>NVIDIA\u00ae GeForce\u00ae 940MX with 2 GB Dedicated Memory\n| sound        = Two speakers\n| input        = SD/SDXC card<br>1 USB 2.0 port<br>USB Type-C<br>HDMI port<br>2 USB 3.0 ports<br>Headphone jack\n| controllers  = \n| camera       = Yes\n| touchpad     = TouchPad\n| connectivity = \n| currentfw    =\n| platform     = \n| service      = \n| dimensions   = 14.59 x 10.09 x 0.79\n| weight       = 4.8 lb\n| topgame      = \n| compatibility= \n| predecessor  = \n| successor    = \n| related      = \n| website      = [http://www.acer.com/ac/en/US/content/series/aspirer15 Acer Aspire R 15]\n}}\nThe Acer Aspire R 15 (model R5-571T-...) is a 15.6 inch convertible (2-in-1) laptop with a mainstream folding design.{{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire S series ==\n'''List of Acer Aspire S series models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n* S3-331\n* S3-371\n* S3-391\n* S3-392\n* S3-392G\n* S3-951\n* S5-371\n* S5-371T\n* S5-391\n* S7-191\n* S7-391\n* S7-392\n* S7-392 (InstantGo)\n* S7-393\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Aspire S3 ===\nThe Acer Aspire S3 is a 13.3-inch Ultrabook with an Intel Core 1.6&nbsp;GHz processor, 320&nbsp;GB hard drive, a media card reader.<ref>[http://us.acer.com/ac/en/US/content/s-series-home Aspire S3 Ultrabook] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502164930/http://us.acer.com/ac/en/US/content/s-series-home|date=May 2, 2012}}, Acer Inc.. Retrieved on 2012-03-17.</ref> Moreover, it has an integrated Intel HD Graphics 3000-chip and four gigabytes of RAM.<ref>[http://www.netzwelt.de/news/91293-acer-aspire-s3-test-guenstiges-ultrabook.html G\u00fcnstiges Ultrabook f\u00fcr Einsteiger: Acer Aspire S3 im Test] (german). Retrieved on 2012-03-17.</ref> Overall, the Ultrabook weighs 2.98 pounds.\n\n=== Aspire S5 ===\nThe Acer Aspire S5 is a 13.3-Inch Ultrabook, which the company says is the world's thinnest Ultrabook.<ref>[http://us.acer.com/ac/en/US/press/2012/28709 Acer Unveils World's Thinnest Ultrabook: Aspire S5] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419043750/http://us.acer.com/ac/en/US/press/2012/28709 |date=2012-04-19 }}, Acer Inc. Retrieved on 2012-02-17.</ref> It is just 15mm-thick and so two millimeters thinner than the [[MacBook Air]].<ref>[http://t3n.de/news/acer-legt-vor-ultradunnes-aspire-356613/ Acer presents: Ultra-thin notebook and Aspire S5 Full-HD Quad Core Tablet Iconia A700] (german), t3n. Retrieved on 2012-03-17.</ref> It weighs 2.97 pounds and includes an Intel Ivy Bridge processor, 8&nbsp;GB of DDR3 RAM, SSD storage for speed and increased shock resistance plus professionally tuned Dolby\u00ae Home Theater\u00ae v4.\n\n=== Aspire S7 ===\nThe Acer Aspire S7 is a 13.3-inch ultrabook, a successor to the Aspire S5. It uses the same aluminum frame wrapping a pearly white plastic and Gorilla Glass encasement and is able to bend backwards 180 degrees and lie flat. It weighs roughly less than 1.3&nbsp;kg and includes an Intel Ivy Bridge processor, 8&nbsp;GB of DDR3 RAM, SSD storage for speed and increased shock resistance plus professionally tuned Dolby Home Theater\u00ae v4.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnet.com/products/acer-aspire-s7-392-6411/|title=Acer Aspire S7-392-6411 review|publisher=Cnet}}</ref>\n\n=== Aspire S13 ===\nThe Acer Aspire S13 is a 13.3-inch ultrabook, a successor to the Aspire S7. The computer has an Intel Core i5 dual-core processor, 1080p display, SSD storage, [[USB-C]] port, and 8GB of ram.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/laptop-reviews/acer-aspire-s-13-2016-review/|title=Acer Aspire S 13 (2016) review|date=15 June 2016|website=Digital Trends|last1=Smith|first1=Matt|accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire Timeline series == \n{{Main|Acer Aspire Timeline}}\nAcer [[Aspire Timeline]] is a discontinued sub-line of the Aspire series which consisted of [[ultrabook]]s. The indirect successor to the Aspire Timeline's are the [[Acer Swift]] lineup.  {{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire V Nitro series ==\n'''List of Acer Aspire V Nitro series models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n*VN7-571\n*VN7-571G\n*VN7-572\n*VN7-572G\n*VN7-572TG\n*VN7-591G\n*VN7-592G\n*VN7-593G\n*VN7-791G\n*VN7-792G\n*VN7-793G{{div col end}}\n\n== Aspire V series ==\n'''List of Acer Aspire V series models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n*V3-111P\n*V3-112P\n*V3-331\n*V3-371\n*V3-372\n*V3-372T\n*V3-431\n*V3-471\n*V3-471G\n*V3-472\n*V3-472G\n*V3-472P\n*V3-472PG\n*V3-531\n*V3-531G\n*V3-532\n*V3-532G\n*V3-551\n*V3-551G\n*V3-571\n*V3-571G\n*V3-572\n*V3-572G\n*V3-572P\n*V3-572PG\n*V3-574\n*V3-574G\n*V3-574T\n*V3-574TG\n*V3-575\n*V3-575G\n*V3-575T\n*V3-575TG\n*V3-731\n*V3-731G\n*V3-771\n*V3-7710\n*V3-7710G\n*V3-771G\n*V3-772G\n* V5-121\n* V5-122P\n* V5-123\n* V5-131\n* V5-132\n* V5-132P\n* V5-171\n* V5-431\n* V5-431G\n* V5-431P\n* V5-431PG\n* V5-452G\n* V5-452PG\n* V5-471\n* V5-471G\n* V5-471P\n* V5-471PG\n* V5-472\n* V5-472G\n* V5-472P\n* V5-472PG\n* V5-473\n* V5-473G\n* V5-473P\n* V5-473PG\n* V5-531\n* V5-531G\n* V5-531P\n* V5-531PG\n* V5-551\n* V5-551G\n* V5-552\n* V5-552G\n* V5-552P\n* V5-552PG\n* V5-561\n* V5-561G\n* V5-561P\n* V5-561PG\n* V5-571\n* V5-571G\n* V5-571P\n* V5-571PG\n* V5-572\n* V5-572G\n* V5-572P\n* V5-572PG\n* V5-573\n* V5-573G\n* V5-573P\n* V5-573PG\n* V5-591G\n* V7-481\n* V7-481G\n* V7-481P\n* V7-481PG\n* V7-482P\n* V7-482PG\n* V7-581\n* V7-581G\n* V7-581P\n* V7-581PG\n* V7-582P\n* V7-582PG\n{{div col end}}The Acer Aspire V series consists of the Acer Aspire V, Acer Aspire V3, Acer Aspire V5, Acer Aspire V 13 and Acer Aspire V15.\n\n=== Aspire V5 ===\n[[File:Acer Aspire V5 20121030.jpg|thumb|Acer Aspire V5]]\n\nThe Acer Aspire V5 is notebook available in 14 and 15.6 inches and comes with a silver scratch resistant exterior. It is considerably slim and is offered in both 10-point multi-touch and non-touch variants. The V5 comes with a HD display with a resolution of 1366\u00d7768 pixels and a webcam on top. The left consists of a power slot, the heat-sink, a proprietary slot to plug-in the adaptor for the Gigabit Ethernet port and the VGA port, an HDMI slot, a USB 3.0 port, two USB 2.0 ports and a 3.5&nbsp;mm headphone jack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultrabooked.com/reviews/1/acer-aspire-v5-specs-review|title=Acer Aspire V5 specs review - Ultrabooked|website=www.ultrabooked.com|access-date=2018-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170428072658/http://www.ultrabooked.com/reviews/1/acer-aspire-v5-specs-review|archive-date=2017-04-28|url-status=dead}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n== Aspire VX series ==\n\n=== Aspire VX 15 ===\nThe Acer Aspire VX 15 specifications includes the use of either an Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 i5-7300HQ or an Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 i7-7700HQ, 8GB or 16GB DDR4 SDRAM, a 15.6\" Full HD (1920 x 1080) 16:9 and either a NVIDIA\u00ae GeForce\u00ae GTX 1050 with 4 GB Dedicated Memory or a NVIDIA\u00ae GeForce\u00ae GTX 1050Ti with 4 GB Dedicated Memory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.acer.com/ac/en/US/content/models/laptops/aspirevx15|title=Laptops {{!}} View All Our Laptops {{!}} Acer Solutions|website=www.acer.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-06}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n=== Aspire VX 5 ===\nThe Acer Aspire VX 5 specifications includes the use of either an Intel Core i7-7700HQ, 8GB DDR4 SDRAM, single-channel, a 15.6 inch 16:9, 1920 x 1080 pixel 141 PPI HD and either a NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1050 Ti (Laptop) - 4096 MB, Core: 1493 - 1620&nbsp;MHz.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.acer-us.com/Tm90ZWJvb2skJEFzcGlyZQ==_2_Aspire/|title=Acer Aspire Laptops List  {{!}} View All Our Laptops {{!}} Acer Solutions|website=www.acer-us.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-18}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n== Other models  ==\n'''List of other Acer Aspire models'''<ref name=\":0\" />{{Div col|colwidth=15em|small=no}}\n*One\n*1200\n*1300\n*1350\n*1360\n*1400\n*1410 (11.6\")\n*1420P\n*1430\n*1430Z\n*1500\n*1520\n*1551\n*1640\n*1640Z\n*1650\n*1660\n*1670\n*1680\n*1690\n*1700\n*1710\n*1800\n*